"origin":33889,"position":0},"title":"Ahmad on Divorce: Not obligation to divorce upon parental request","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 16, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Sindi reported: A man asked Abu Abdullah, Imam Ahmad, \u201cMy father has ordered me to divorce my wife.\u201d Ahmad said, \u201cDo not divorce her.\u201d He said, \u201cDid not Umar command his son Abdullah to divorce his wife?\u201d Ahmad said, \u201cIs your father like Umar, may Allah be pleased with him?\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33887,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/01\/06\/condemnation-nikah-halala\/","url_meta":{"origin":33889,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Marriage: Condemnation of Nikah Halala","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 6, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Mas'ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, cursed the one who marries a woman to overturn an irrevocable divorce and the man for whom it is done. Al-Tirmidhi said, \"This tradition was acted upon by the people of knowledge among the companions of\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6555,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/17\/umar-converts-to-islam\/","url_meta":{"origin":33889,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Umar: The Prophet prays for Umar&#8217;s conversion","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 17, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cO Allah, strengthen Islam with one of two men whom you love more: Abu Jahl or Umar ibn al-Khattab.\u201d Ibn Umar said, \u201cThe most beloved of the two was Umar.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 3681 Grade:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33723,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/10\/13\/umar-on-hamd-how-are-you-all-praise-is-due-to-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":33889,"position":3},"title":"Umar on Hamd: How are you? All praise is due to Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 13, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: A man greeted Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, with peace and Umar returned his greeting. Then, Umar said to the man, \u201cHow are you?\u201d The man said, \u201cI praise Allah to you.\u201d Umar said, \u201cThis praise is what I wanted from you.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28987,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/09\/umar-humility-raises-wisdom\/","url_meta":{"origin":33889,"position":4},"title":"Umar on Humility: Allah raises his wisdom if he humbles himself","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 9, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Ubaydullah ibn \u2018Adi reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said upon the pulpit, \u201cVerily, if a servant humbles himself for Allah Almighty, he will increase his wisdom.\u201d Source: Juz\u2019 fi\u0304hi\u0304 H\u0323adi\u0304th Sufya\u0304n ibn \u2018Uyaynah 24 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Ibn Hajar \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064f\u0628\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37577,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/12\/19\/umar-tarak-salah\/","url_meta":{"origin":33889,"position":5},"title":"Umar on Salat: No share of Islam for one who leaves prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 19, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Miswar ibn Makhramah reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cThere is no share of Islam for one who abandons the prayer.\u201d Source: al-Muwat\u0323t\u0323a' 117 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u0650\u0633\u0652\u0648\u064e\u0631 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0645\u064e\u062e\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064e\u0637\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650 \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u062d\u064e\u0638\u0651\u064e \u0641\u0650\u064a\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","w